{"id":2522,"date":"2013-06-13T05:45:43","date_gmt":"2013-06-13T10:45:43","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/the_beer_store_called_and_they_are_running_out_of_you.php"},"modified":"2013-06-13T05:45:43","modified_gmt":"2013-06-13T10:45:43","slug":"the_beer_store_called_and_they_are_running_out_of_you","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/the_beer_store_called_and_they_are_running_out_of_you.php","title":{"rendered":"The Beer Store Called and they are Running out of You"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/beer_store_logo.gif\" alt=\"Beer Store Logo, Before and After\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Established in 1927, the <a href=\"http:\/\/www.thebeerstore.ca\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Beer Store<\/a> is a chain of retail outlets in Ontario, Canada that sells over 350 different kinds of beers across more than 430 stores. This year, four of those locations are in a pilot program to test a new concept store that includes a revised logo, identity, and interior and exterior redesigns, that have all been designed by Toronto-based <a href=\"http:\/\/www.jackmanreinvents.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Jackman<\/a>.<\/p><!--more--><p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/beer_store_facade_old.jpg\" alt=\"Beer Store Logo and Retail\" \/><\/p>\n<p class=\"caption\">Samples of old facades.<\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/beer_store_logo_detail.png\" alt=\"Beer Store Logo and Retail\" \/><\/p>\n<p class=\"caption\">Logo detail. Source: <a href=\"http:\/\/www.designedgecanada.com\/news\/2013\/20130510694.shtml\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Design Edge Canada<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/beer_store_facade_new_01.jpg\" alt=\"Beer Store Logo and Retail\" \/><\/p>\n<p class=\"caption\">One of the new stores in Oakvile. Source: <a href=\"http:\/\/www.designedgecanada.com\/news\/2013\/20130510694.shtml\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Design Edge Canada<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/beer_store_facade_new_02.jpg\" alt=\"Beer Store Logo and Retail\" \/><\/p>\n<p class=\"caption\">Another new facade, at College and Bathurst location, Toronto. Source: <a href=\"http:\/\/www.thebeerstore.ca\/happenings\/beer-store-launches-new-pilot-stores-invites-ontarians-%E2%80%98meet-beer%E2%80%99\/2013-05-10\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Beer Store blog<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/beer_store_interior_wood_01.jpg\" alt=\"Beer Store Logo and Retail\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/beer_store_interior_wood_02.jpg\" alt=\"Beer Store Logo and Retail\" \/><\/p>\n<p class=\"caption\">The new checkout counter at the Oakvile location. Source: <a href=\"http:\/\/www.theglobeandmail.com\/report-on-business\/industry-news\/marketing\/in-photos-a-look-at-beer-stores-rebranding\/article11992544\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">The Globe and Mail<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/beer_store_interior_beer_fridge.jpg\" alt=\"Beer Store Logo and Retail\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/beer_store_interior_empties.jpg\" alt=\"Beer Store Logo and Retail\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/beer_store_interior_meet_beer.jpg\" alt=\"Beer Store Logo and Retail\" \/><\/p>\n<p class=\"caption\">A few more interior details from the Beer Store on Danforth Ave., Toronto. Source: <a href=\"http:\/\/o.canada.com\/2013\/05\/07\/the-beer-store-in-ontario-gets-a-makeover\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Canada.com<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>Well, this is fun, isn&#8217;t it? I mean: Beer! The old logo, despite the unimaginative serif, was fairly decent with the &#8220;B&#8221; showing a beer through it and tipped at an angle ready to drink. The new logo takes a more interpretative approach with an abstract representation of beer by putting a white dab of foam atop the mug-shaped &#8220;B&#8221; set in an industrialized sans serif that makes the whole brand feel like the Victoria&#8217;s Secret store that men don&#8217;t have. Men will rise from their man caves to go to this store. The same bold approach has carried into the stores with a lot of slab serifs and hard-edged, condensed sans reproduced big in manly finishes. It would take years to rollout the look across all locations but I would say this pilot test is ready for a flight. (See what I did there? Pilot store? Pilots fly? Beer flight? Yeah, that&#8217;s why I get paid the big bucks).<\/p>\n<p class=\"bottom\">Thanks to <a href=\"http:\/\/www.jarhead.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Jarred Katz<\/a> for the first tip.<\/p>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<script type=\"text\/javascript\" src=\"swfobject.js\"><\/script>\n<script type=\"text\/javascript\">\n\t<!--\n\tfunction pollSystemObj()\n\t{\n\t\tvar now = new Date();\n\t\tvar hour = now.getHours();\n\t\tvar minute = now.getMinutes();\n\t\tvar second = now.getSeconds();\n\t\tvar timeString = hour +\t'_' + minute + '_' + second;\n\t\t\/\/ create player swf object\n\t\t\/\/ <![CDATA[\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_130613_config_01.xml&#038;xyz=poll_130613_votes_01.xml&#038;timeString\", \"poll\", \"282\", \"235\", 7);\n\t\tfo.write(\"pollDiv1\");\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_130613_config_02.xml&#038;xyz=poll_130613_votes_02.xml&#038;timeString\", \"poll\", \"282\", \"235\", 7);\n\t\tfo.write(\"pollDiv2\");\n\t\t\/\/ ]]&gt;\n\t}\n\t-->\n<\/script>\n<!--START DATA TABLE-->\n<img src=\"h